data.content:
Three breaking changes hit your code. Here's each one:

---

### 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` ŌĆö now accepts a regular lambda, not an expression tree

Your manual `Expression.Lambda`/`Expression.Call` code **won't compile** because a new non-expression `Func<>` overload is preferred. Replace the entire block with:

```csharp
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

No more expression tree manipulation needed.

---

### 2. Complex type column names ŌĆö now auto-uniquified & nested paths changed

**Two sub-changes:**

- **Uniquification:** `ShippingAddress.Street` and `BillingAddress.Street` previously silently shared one column. EF 10 appends a number (e.g. `Street`, `Street1`). If you have an existing DB schema, add explicit `HasColumnName` to preserve the old mapping:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress,
        p => p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("Street"));
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress,
        p => p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("Street"));
});
```

- **Nested full-path naming:** `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` was previously column `BillingAddress_City`. It's now `Payment_BillingAddress_City`. To keep the old name:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Order>()
    .ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment)
    .ComplexProperty(p => p.BillingAddress)
    .Property(a => a.City)
    .HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City");
```

ŌÜĀ’ĖÅ **Both of these will generate migrations that rename/add columns if left unaddressed**, potentially causing data loss.

---

### 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` ŌĆö new `logCommandText` parameter

Every method gains a `string logCommandText` parameter (for redacted SQL logging). Update your signature:

```csharp
public class MyLogger : IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger
{
    public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
        IRelationalConnection connection,
        DbCommand command,
        DbContext context,
        Guid commandId,
        Guid connectionId,
        DateTimeOffset startTime,
        string logCommandText)   // ŌåÉ new parameter
    {
        // Use logCommandText for logging (sensitive data redacted)
        // Use command.CommandText for actual SQL
    }
}
```

Update all method overrides on this interface similarly (`CommandReaderExecuted`, `CommandScalarExecuting`, etc.).
